    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-10-06T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-10-06T11:00:00-05:00" n="627"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d627">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795A.5/10–650: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Denmark</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Anderson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Copenhagen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-10-06T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 6, 1950—5 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 6—1:36 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>357. <gloss target="#t_Depcirtel1">Depcirtel</gloss> 9, October 5. We have no
                    information which would throw light on intentions Chinese Communists or Soviet
                    Union re Korea.</p>
                <p>Foreign Office not yet in code telegraph communication with Denmark Minister
                    Peking and latter’s despatches show restraint owing to lack of safe courier
                    service.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Anderson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
